            "answer_text": "There is no such measure, because everyone will have different opinions.   Let's take the history of the second half of the 20th century, for example, where the following innovations all have legitimate claims to be the most important invention of the time, though there won't be unanimous agreement on which comes in first.  The transistorThe jet engineTelevisionSpace flightComputersEnvironmentalismCivil rightsThe InternetGlobalizationVenture capitalSilicon ValleyEtc.",
